claim.claim-text:
1. A method of monitoring a status of an air filter of an HVAC system, wherein the HVAC system has a fan for driving air through the air filter of the HVAC system, the method comprising:
a) turning the fan “off” so that substantially no air is driven through the air filter;
b) with the fan “off”, measuring a sensor offset differential pressure value between an upstream side of the air filter and a downstream side of the air filter;
c) storing the sensor offset differential value;
d) turning the fan “on” so that air is driven through the air filter;
e) with the fan “on”, measuring an un-compensated differential pressure value between the upstream side of the air filter and the downstream side of the air filter;
f) determining a compensated differential pressure value by removing the sensor offset differential value from the un-compensated differential pressure value;
g) determining the status of the air filter based, at least in part, on the compensated differential pressure value; and
h) displaying the status of the air filter on a display of an HVAC controller.

14. A method of monitoring a status of an air filter of an HVAC system, wherein the HVAC system has a fan for driving air through the air filter of the HVAC system, the method comprising:
operating the HVAC system in a heating mode, cooling mode or ventilation mode;
occasionally entering an air filter monitoring mode, wherein the air filter monitoring mode includes:
turning the fan of the HVAC system “off” so that substantially no air is driven through the air filter;
with the fan “off”, measuring a sensor offset differential pressure value between an upstream side of the air filter and a downstream side of the air filter;
storing the sensor offset differential value;

occasionally entering an air filter monitoring mode, wherein the air filter monitoring mode includes:
turning the fan “on” so that air is driven through the air filter;
with the fan “on”, measuring an un-compensated differential pressure value between the upstream side of the air filter and the downstream side of the air filter;
determining a compensated differential pressure value by removing the stored sensor offset differential value from the un-compensated differential pressure value;
determining the status of the air filter based, at least in part, on the compensated differential pressure value;
displaying the status of the air filter on a display of an HVAC controller.

17. An HVAC controller for monitoring a status of an air filter of an HVAC system, wherein the HVAC system has a fan for driving air through the air filter of the HVAC system, the HVAC controller comprising:
a controller;
a memory coupled to the controller;
a display coupled to the controller;
wherein the controller is programmed to:
send a command to turn the fan of the HVAC system “off” so that substantially no air is driven through the air filter;
with the fan “off”, obtain a sensor offset differential pressure value that is representative of a sensed pressure between an upstream side of the air filter and a downstream side of the air filter;
store the sensor offset differential value in the memory;
send a command to turn the fan of the HVAC system “on” so that air is driven through the air filter;
with the fan “on”, obtain an un-compensated differential pressure value that is representative of a sensed pressure between the upstream side of the air filter and the downstream side of the air filter;
determine a compensated differential pressure value by removing the sensor offset differential value from the un-compensated differential pressure value;
determining the status of the air filter based, at least in part, on the compensated differential pressure value; and
displaying the status of the air filter on a display.
